<LP>
   McCONNELLSBURG, Pa. -- JLG Industries Inc. said that
despite recent softening in orders, it expects to post record
net income and sales for the year ended July 31. The company
didn't disclose specific figures.
   For fiscal 1989, the hydraulic machinery concern had net
income of $7.5 million on sales of $121.3 million.
