   FINANCIAL SERVICES
                                                                                                       

       2ND QTR. 1990           2ND QTR. 1989       % CHG.
                                                                                                       

        6,414,449               7,999,244          - 20
                                                                                                       

   Many insurers saw their property/casualty results shrink.
Pricing continues soft as companies vie for commercial
business. Higher earnings in the group health insurance area
boosted results for several of the multiline insurers. For
life insurance companies, better interest-rate spreads,
expense reduction and a continued decline in policy
cancellations helped improve profitability.
   Kemper took $161.1 million in special charges. Cigna said
the poor conditions in the property/casualty market will
constrain its results this year and in 1991. It expects to
take a charge of no more than $65 million as it accelerates
the consolidation of some offices. Aetna benefited from gains
in its group health insurance and its pension and investment
businesses.
   Securities firms' profits rebounded a bit from a depressed
first quarter, with Merrill Lynch and Salomon reporting a
modest revival in investment-banking revenue. But
year-to-year profit comparisons were poor because 1989's
second quarter was particularly strong. Despite the rebound
at Merrill and Salomon, investment-banking and underwriting
revenue at most firms stand at six-year lows. Many securities
firms continued to increase the customer assets they manage,
which rake in steady fees.
   But even near-record levels in the stock market couldn't
revive sluggish trading, a revival that analysts say is
necessary to jump-start the flagging earnings at many big
firms. This quarter won't be much better for many brokers,
particularly compared with 1989's strong third quarter,
analysts say.
                                                                                                       

