   UTILITIES
                                                                                                       

        2ND QTR. 1990         2ND QTR. 1989        % CHG.
                                                                                                       

         5,666,558             6,360,115           - 11
                                                                                                       

   United Telecom's local phone business remained strong, but
profit was hurt by big losses at long-distance unit US
Sprint. At other carriers, regulatory changes and sluggish
regional economies hampered earnings. Profit at Southern New
England Telecommunications slumped on slow growth in its
Connecticut base and a 5% cut in rates. Contel was bruised by
a first-quarter acquisition of some McCaw Cellular
Communications properties. But Centel gained from traffic
growth as well as reduced interest expense.
                                                                                                       

