<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   OKLAHOMA CITY -- Petroleum Investments Ltd. said it
successfully completed an exchange offer in which a recently
formed affiliate, Bradmar Petroleum Corp., swapped one-tenth
of a share of common for each Petroleum Investments
depositary unit outstanding.
   Petroleum Investments, an oil and gas master limited
partnership, said 13.4 million depositary units, or about
79.9% of the total outstanding, were tendered to Bradmar. It
added that Bradmar also received and will accept tenders of
limited partner interests in nine affiliated limited
partnerships, representing an aggregate of $1.9 million of
exchange value.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The two companies expect to complete their consolidation
Tuesday, Petroleum Investments said, adding that Bradmar
common will begin trading on the American Stock Exchange
Wednesday under the symbol BPC.
