<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Student Loan Marketing Association, or
Sallie Mae, said it will price $600 million in short-term
floating-rate notes due Feb. 14, 1991.
   Settlement of the notes will occur Thursday. When-issued
trading is expected to begin at 8:20 a.m. Tuesday.
</LP>
