<HL>
   Business Brief -- ADT Ltd.:
   Canada's Laidlaw Inc. Raises
   Stake to 28.8%, From 27.7%
</HL>
<DATE>
08/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LDMFA LDM.B ADTLY CP T.CP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Laidlaw Inc. said it increased its holdings in ADT Ltd. to
28.8%, from 27.7%.
   The transaction, which has an indicated value of $34.1
million, brings Laidlaw's stake in ADT to about 284.6 million
common shares.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The shares were acquired from Michael Ashcroft, a director
of ADT. Laidlaw granted Mr. Ashcroft an option to repurchase
the stock at the price the company paid for it, $3.10 a
share, for a period ending Dec. 31, 1999 -- an agreement
Laidlaw can terminate on six months' notice any time after
Jan. 15, 1993.
   A spokesman for Laidlaw said the Burlington, Ontario-based
transportation and waste-services concern would continue to
evaluate market and economic conditions before deciding to
purchase additional stock in ADT.
   Laidlaw earlier indicated it would be reluctant to
increase its stake in ADT beyond 30% because of British
takeover regulations that require a company acquiring more
than a 30% holding to extend an offer to the rest of the
company's holders.
   ADT is a Bermuda-based security services and auctions
concern. Laidlaw is 47%-controlled by Canadian Pacific Ltd.,
a Montreal transportation, resources and industrial holding
concern.
</TEXT>
